Competencies

Now it’s time to write apps with persistent memory, a simple example of which would be a blog
Sinatra doesn’t have a built-in database, you can use gems such as PostgreSQL and SQLite to remedy that with one line of code
Sinatra handles ActiveRecord with Rake, just as we have been using before
Data from the database (model) integrates seamlessly and is served up by a route handler (controller) to the browser (view) 

